insert into `p18Data` (`id`, `cid`, `schemeid`, `value`) values('12-3B-8A','119','59','Darryl Wood interviews John Conyers about such questions as whether civil rights policies now overlook the needs of African-Americans and whether the greater focus on women and homosexuals dilutes the cause of blacks.  He asks him such questions as whether we really need to continue to fight for enforcement of civil rights, how we can look at changing peoplesâ€™ present-day perceptions, issues of concern about where the funding for civil rights is going, and how we can maintain progressive action for black Americans.  Conyers responds to such questions by conveying his belief that we must recognize that we are moving into an era of human rights rather than just civil rights, and that even though other aspects of the civil rights struggle are obscuring African-American causes, blacks still are predominant in most of the groups that are being fought for.  In addition, he discusses what we should be doing to maintain progressive action and how such controversial and confusing issues such as reparations should be approached.');
